<section id="authzframe-pip-X509Bootstrap" xreflabel="X509 Bootstrap PIP"> <title>X509Bootstrap</title>
 
 <section><title>Class name</title>
  <para><filename>org.globus.wsrf.impl.security.authorization.X509BootstrapPIP</filename></para>
 </section>
 
 <section><title>Overview</title>
  <para> This implements the BootstrapPIP interface [PIP-glossary] which is used when X509 Certificates are used during authentication scheme. 
   It collects peer entities' attributes obtained from the certificates presented by the peer.</para>
 </section>
 
 <section><title>Configuration</title>
  <para>No configuration is required.</para>
 </section>
 
 <section><title>Attributes Collected</title>
  <para>The attributes collected by this PIP are the following:</para>
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem><para>Description of attribute</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para>Identity attribute</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para>Attribute ID</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para>Datatype</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para>Issuer</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para>Validity from</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para>Validity to</para></listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  
<section><title>Example I</title>
 
<orderedlist>
 <listitem><para>Peer's Subject object</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Identity attribute</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Constants.SUBJECT_ATTRIBUTE_ID</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Constants.SUBJECT_DATATYPE_URI</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Container</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Current time</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Infinity</para></listitem>
</orderedlist>

</section>
  
<section><title>Example II</title>
 <orderedlist>
  <listitem><para>Peer's principals</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Identity attribute</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Constants.PRINCIPAL_ATTRIBUTE_ID</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Constants.PRINCIPAL_DATATYPE_URI</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Container</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Current time</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Infinity</para></listitem>
 </orderedlist>
</section>
 </section>
 
 <section><title>Related interceptors</title>
  <para> If X509 Certificates are used for authentication, this bootstrap is
   used by the Authorization Framework by default.</para>
 </section>
</section>
